import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["values"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["values"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.astype({'width': 'float', 'height': 'float'})
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='width', y='height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between width and height in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x=data['values'])
    plt.axvline(x=data['values'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the average value in the volcano dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
